29#include "dmacnv50.h"
30#include "rootnv50.h"
31
32#include <core/client.h>
33
34#include <nvif/class.h>
35#include <nvif/unpack.h>
36
37int
38nv50_disp_base_new(const struct nv50_disp_dmac_func *func,
39 const struct nv50_disp_chan_mthd *mthd,
40 struct nv50_disp_root *root, int chid,
41 const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, void *data, u32 size,
42 struct nvkm_object **pobject)
43{
44 union {
45 struct nv50_disp_base_channel_dma_v0 v0;
46 } *args = data;
47 struct nvkm_object *parent = oclass->parent;
48 struct nv50_disp *disp = root->disp;
49 int head, ret;
50 u64 push;
51
52 nvif_ioctl(parent, "create disp base channel dma size %d\n", size);
53 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
54 nvif_ioctl(parent, "create disp base channel dma vers %d "
55 "pushbuf %016"PRIx64" head %d\n",
56 args->v0.version, args->v0.pushbuf, args->v0.head);
57 if (args->v0.head > disp->base.head.nr)
58 return -EINVAL;
59 push = args->v0.pushbuf;
60 head = args->v0.head;
61 } else
62 return ret;
63
64 return nv50_disp_dmac_new_(func, mthd, root, chid + head,
65 head, push, oclass, pobject);
66}

69nv50_disp_base_mthd_base = {
70 .mthd = 0x0000,
71 .addr = 0x000000,
72 .data = {

78 { 0x0094, 0x610884 },
79 { 0x00a0, 0x6108a0 },
80 { 0x00a4, 0x610878 },
81 { 0x00c0, 0x61086c },
82 { 0x00e0, 0x610858 },
83 { 0x00e4, 0x610860 },
84 { 0x00e8, 0x6108ac },

99 { 0x0804, 0x6108fc },

107static const struct nv50_disp_chan_mthd
108nv50_disp_base_chan_mthd = {
109 .name = "Base",
110 .addr = 0x000540,
111 .prev = 0x000004,
112 .data = {
113 { "Global", 1, &nv50_disp_base_mthd_base },

115 {}
